                "SISD",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Emitted particles and fission",
                "fragments were detected in the Silicon Telescope",
                "Array for Reaction Studies  (STARS).",
                "The STARS array is comprised of a series of",
                "double-sided, annular Si detectors for particle",
                "detection. Each detector is segmented into 48 rings",
                "and 16 sectors; adjacent rings and sectors are",
                "combined for a total of 24 rings and 8 sectors. The",
                "array consisted of two detector telescopes downstream",
                "of the target for reaction channel identification,",
                "and a third telescope, upstream from the target, for",
                "fission tagging. The downstream detectors consisted",
                "of 150mu-m and 1003 mu-m thick detectors,",
                "respectively. This telescope array covered a range of",
                "31deg to 61deg at forward angles, relative to the",
                "beam axis. The third detector, 140 mu-m thick, was",
                "placed 8.9-mm upstream of the target for fission",
                "tagging. This detector subtended angles of 142deg to",
                "165deg relative to the beam axis."
              ]
            }
